 leflunomide''s active metabolite from plasma, which otherwise may take up to two years.', 'Synergism', 'Rabeprazole, Misoprostol, Chondroitin sulfate, Glucosamine, Esomeprazole', 'Golimumab, Ustekinumab, Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Tocilizumab, Secukinumab, Canakinumab, Anifrolumab, Ravulizumab, Diroximel fumarate, Mycophenolic acid, Abatacept, More', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/170273/', '[1] "Product Information. Arava (leflunomide)." Hoechst Marion-Roussel Inc, Kansas City, MO.[2] "Product Information. Aubagio (teriflunomide)." Genzyme Corporation, Cambridge, MA.[3] EMEA "EMEA public statement on leflunomide (ARAVA) - severe and serious hepatic reactions. Available from URL: http://www.eudra.org/emea.html." ([1999 Sept 2]):', 1767369485);
